                     </handNote>
            </handDesc>
                  <additions>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                           <locus/>
                           <p>Foll. 226, 227, and 228, are three leaves from another copy of the
                              same work, of about the same age.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                           <locus/>
                           <p>On fol. 1 b we find the name of a former possessor, and on fol. 229 b,
                              that of another.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="ar">قد ملك علي هذا الكتاب قس عبد المسيح ابن
                      ....<locus from="1b"/></quote>
                           </p>
                          <p>
                            <quote xml:lang="ar">صاحبه شماس خدر ابن شاهين الحايك.<locus from="229b"/></quote>
                          </p>
                        </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <locus/>
                  <p>On fol. 2 a we read in the handwriting of <persName>Colonel Taylor</persName>,
                    " <persName>R. Taylor</persName>. <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/41"
                      >Bagdad</placeName>. <date calendar="Gregorian" when="1843-01-01">1 January
                      1843</date>. Vocabulary Syriac and Arabic. Garshunic;" and on fol. 3 a, "
                    Kitab oot Tarjuman fi. Taaleem Loghat is Soorian."</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
                  
                  
